Here's a reproducible test case, with a path of "/" and version 1 the cookie is not persisted in IE, with the same path and no version the cookie is persisted.  Both cookies are persisted in FireFox

<%@ page import="javax.servlet.http.*" %>
<%
Cookie[] myCookies = request.getCookies();

  for(int n=0; myCookies!=null && n < myCookies.length; n++)
  {
    out.print(myCookies[n].getName() + " : ");
    out.print(myCookies[n].getValue() + "<BR>");
  }

 Cookie version0Cookie = new Cookie(
		 "TestCookiev0" + (new java.util.Date()).getTime(),
